content:
Minimal fix: add the same 30s skew tolerance at expiry check.

```js
const CLOCK_SKEW_MS = 30_000;

if (expMs + CLOCK_SKEW_MS < nowMs) {
  return res.status(401).json({ error: 'expired_token' });
}
```

Regression test:
- mock `verifyJwt()` to return `{ sub: 'u1', exp: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) - 29 }`
- expect `next()` to be called, not `res.status(401)`

Optional boundary case:
- `{ exp: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) - 31 }` -> expect 401.

```js
async function loadUser(id, next) {
  if (!id) return next(new Error('missing_id'));

  try {
    const user = await db.findUser(id);
    if (!user) return next(new Error('not_found'));

    await audit.log(user.id);
    await cache.set(user.id, user);

    next(null, user);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
}
```

If `db.findUser`, `audit.log`, or `cache.set` are still callback-based, wrap them with `util.promisify` first; keep the `if (!id)` and `if (!user)` checks exactly in this order.
